<p>I hate this and am upvoting, so you've done a good job at it. A few thoughts:</p>
<p>Note #3 is a little confusing - I'm interpreting that as &quot;Yea, we backed the South because we had slave, but now that they've lost we're backing the North.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Nota Bene: Given the recent political developments, <strong>particularly the recent war between the states</strong> and its implications for the likely future of Negro servitude, alternate plans are being composed for the future of the Drapetomaniac Class, upon which our research has become rather dependent. —Director Wilson, noted October 4th <strong>1862</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p>In 1862, it was the CURRENT war between the states (or “this awful war” or “Civil War” - <a href="http://deadconfederates.com/2011/06/21/the-war-of-northern-aggression-is-modern-segregationist-revisionism/">&quot;The War of Northern Aggression&quot; is used only in modern times</a> and Google is awesome!)</p>

