			<div class="content" id="post-content-1328676">
									

<p>I'm from alabama, and I've never heard anyone say that but douchey hipsters being ironic.</p>
<p>Okay, so.</p>
<p>This is damn well written, believable, and actually plausible for its period. That said, at no point does the page specify that it has been debunked outside the page title, and for that I must downvote.</p>
<p>You see, SCP-EX entries are SCPs that have been explained or rendered inert. While you know and I know that IRL no one believes this spew in the present age, the page never <em>says</em> that. Without a segment detailing how and why it was proved incorrect, this page stands alone in its canon as an SCP type article saying that black people are inferior in the most blunt and ignorant way possible, and I don't think that's okay. Poor taste aside, the way this article is formatted implies that the Foundation <em>continues to believe this</em>.</p>
<p>Add a disclaimer, in character, not out, and it will be a -EX. As it stands, it's just racism as an SCP, and my downvote reflects that.</p>

